House Resolution 235
By: Representatives Gambill of the 15th and Scoggins of the 14th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Hickory Log upon the occasion of its 55th anniversary; and
2 for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, established in White, Georgia, in 1970, Hickory Log is a private non-profit
4 personal care living facility for men with special needs, including intellectual disabilities,
5 developmental disabilities, and traumatic brain injuries; and
6 WHEREAS, founded by Al and Sara Munn for their son, Rey, and the men in surrounding
7 counties, this outstanding organization provides a safe space for residents to hone their
8 relational, vocational, and financial skills in a manner that champions independence within
9 the personal care home model; and
10 WHEREAS, recognizing that families wish to keep their loved ones close, Hickory Log not
11 only offers comprehensive care to its residents but also extends support and community to
12 their families; and
13 WHEREAS, Hickory Log is benevolently committed to loving all people with a heart of
14 compassion, service, and grace; and
